                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d363">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">835.00 Revolutions/5: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Argentina</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bliss</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Buenos Aires</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-09-09T15:00:00-04:00"
                            >September 9, 1930—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 4:51 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>126. Have received official note, signed Ernesto Bosch and dated yesterday,
                    advising me that, as a result of event of public note, General <pb facs="0462"
                        n="382" xml:id="pg_382"/> Uriburu has assumed “Provisional Presidency of the
                    nation” with the aims set forth in manifesto of the 6th and giving a list of his
                    Cabinet. He also states: “It is the purpose and desire of the Provisional
                    Government to maintain and develop as far as possible the cordial relations
                    which happily unite the Argentine Republic with the nation that you so worthily
                    represent.”</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bliss</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
